          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Using the Azure CLI in Scripts"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Interactive az commands are fine for exploration, but the real power of the Azure CLI emerges in automation: repeatable provisioning, scheduled operations, CI/CD pipelines, and infrastructure-as-code workflows. Scripting the CLI requires understanding how to handle exit codes, capture output, handle failures, and write scripts that are safe to run more than once."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
