      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Check exit code explicitly when --query returns null\nif ! az storage account show -g myRG -n mysa --query name -o tsv 2>/dev/null; then\n  echo \"Storage account does not exist yet\"\nfi\n\n# Capture and inspect exit code\naz vm start -g myRG -n myVM\nstatus=$?\nif [[ $status -ne 0 ]]; then\n  echo \"VM start failed with code $status\" >&2\n  exit $status\nfi"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Idempotent Resource Creation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A script that can be run multiple times without error or duplication is called idempotent. Azure resource creation commands fail with an error if the resource already exists\u2014unless you guard against it."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Create-or-Skip Pattern"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nRG=\"${RG:-myRG}\"\nLOCATION=\"${LOCATION:-eastus}\"\nSA_NAME=\"${SA_NAME:-mystorage123}\"\n\n# Create resource group only if it doesn't exist\nif ! az group show --name \"$RG\" --output none 2>/dev/null; then\n  echo \"Creating resource group: $RG\"\n  az group create --name \"$RG\" --location \"$LOCATION\"\nelse\n  echo \"Resource group already exists: $RG\"\nfi\n\n# Storage accounts: --only-show-errors suppresses noisy warnings\nif ! az storage account show --name \"$SA_NAME\" -g \"$RG\" --output none 2>/dev/null; then\n  az storage account create \\\n    --name \"$SA_NAME\" \\\n    --resource-group \"$RG\" \\\n    --location \"$LOCATION\" \\\n    --sku Standard_LRS \\\n    --kind StorageV2 \\\n    --only-show-errors\nfi"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "az resource list for Generic Existence Checks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Check if any resource with a given name exists in the subscription\nresource_exists() {\n  local name=$1 type=$2\n  local count\n  count=$(az resource list --name \"$name\" --resource-type \"$type\" \\\n    --query \"length(@)\" -o tsv 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n  [[ \"$count\" -gt 0 ]]\n}\n\nif resource_exists myKeyVault Microsoft.KeyVault/vaults; then\n  echo \"Key Vault exists, skipping creation\"\nelse\n  az keyvault create -n myKeyVault -g myRG -l eastus\nfi"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Capturing Output in Scripts"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scripting the CLI means taking output from one command and feeding it into the next. The critical rule: always use -o tsv for single values and -o json for structured data. Never parse table output."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Capturing Single Values"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Capture resource ID\nWEBAPP_ID=$(az webapp show -g myRG -n myApp --query id -o tsv)\n\n# Capture connection string\nCONN_STR=$(az storage account show-connection-string \\\n  -g myRG -n mysa --query connectionString -o tsv)\n\n# Capture and immediately use\nPRINCIPAL_ID=$(az webapp identity assign -g myRG -n myApp \\\n  --query principalId -o tsv)\n\naz keyvault set-policy -n myKV \\\n  --object-id \"$PRINCIPAL_ID\" \\\n  --secret-permissions get list"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Capturing Arrays and Iterating"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Iterate over all VMs in a resource group\nwhile IFS= read -r vm_name; do\n  echo \"Processing: $vm_name\"\n  az vm get-instance-view -g myRG -n \"$vm_name\" \\\n    --query \"instanceView.statuses[?starts_with(code,'PowerState/')].displayStatus\" \\\n    -o tsv\ndone < <(az vm list -g myRG --query \"[*].name\" -o tsv)\n\n# Parallel operations with background jobs\naz vm list -g myRG --query \"[*].name\" -o tsv | while read -r vm; do\n  az vm start -g myRG -n \"$vm\" --no-wait &\ndone\nwait\necho \"All VMs started (no-wait)\"\n\n# Cap parallelism at 4 concurrent operations using xargs\naz vm list -g myRG --query \"[*].name\" -o tsv |\nxargs -P4 -I{} az vm stop -g myRG -n {} --no-wait"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reading Multiple Fields"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Destructure multiple fields from TSV output\nwhile IFS=$'\\t' read -r name location sku; do\n  printf \"%-30s  %-15s  %s\\n\" \"$name\" \"$location\" \"$sku\"\ndone < <(az storage account list -g myRG \\\n  --query \"[*].[name,location,sku.name]\" -o tsv)\n\n# Store as associative array\ndeclare -A vm_sizes\nwhile IFS=$'\\t' read -r name size; do\n  vm_sizes[\"$name\"]=$size\ndone < <(az vm list -g myRG --query \"[*].[name,hardwareProfile.vmSize]\" -o tsv)\n\nfor vm in \"${!vm_sizes[@]}\"; do\n  echo \"$vm -> ${vm_sizes[$vm]}\"\ndone"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Error Handling and Rollback"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Production scripts must clean up partial state when something goes wrong. The bash trap command executes a function when the script exits\u2014whether normally or due to an error\u2014making it the right place to delete temporary resources."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Using trap for Cleanup"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nTMP_RG=\"deploy-temp-$$\"    # $$ is the PID, unique per run\nCLEANUP_DONE=false\n\ncleanup() {\n  if [[ \"$CLEANUP_DONE\" == \"false\" ]]; then\n    echo \"Cleaning up temporary resource group: $TMP_RG\" >&2\n    az group delete --name \"$TMP_RG\" --yes --no-wait 2>/dev/null || true\n    CLEANUP_DONE=true\n  fi\n}\n\n# Run cleanup on any exit (0 or non-zero)\ntrap cleanup EXIT\n\n# Create staging resources\naz group create -n \"$TMP_RG\" -l eastus\naz storage account create -n tmpsa$$ -g \"$TMP_RG\" --sku Standard_LRS\n\n# Deploy to production\naz webapp deployment source config-zip \\\n  -g prodRG -n myApp --src ./app.zip\n\n# If we reach here without error, promote and skip cleanup\nCLEANUP_DONE=true\naz group delete --name \"$TMP_RG\" --yes --no-wait\necho \"Deployment complete.\" "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retry Logic for Transient Failures"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Retry a command up to N times with exponential backoff\naz_with_retry() {\n  local max_attempts=${AZ_RETRY_MAX:-4}\n  local delay=2\n  local attempt=1\n  while [[ $attempt -le $max_attempts ]]; do\n    if \"$@\"; then\n      return 0\n    fi\n    if [[ $attempt -lt $max_attempts ]]; then\n      echo \"Attempt $attempt failed. Retrying in ${delay}s...\" >&2\n      sleep \"$delay\"\n      delay=$((delay * 2))\n    fi\n    ((attempt++))\n  done\n  echo \"All $max_attempts attempts failed: $*\" >&2\n  return 1\n}\n\n# Use it for operations that may transiently fail\naz_with_retry az webapp start -g myRG -n myApp"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Script Configuration Patterns"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scripts that are called from CI/CD pipelines need a clear interface: what variables do they require, what optional variables can override defaults, and how should callers know the script succeeded?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Environment Variable Interface"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\n# Required: fail fast with a clear message if missing\n: \"${AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID:?AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID is required}\"\n: \"${TARGET_RG:?TARGET_RG is required}\"\n\n# Optional with defaults (${VAR:-default} syntax)\nLOCATION=\"${LOCATION:-eastus}\"\nVM_SIZE=\"${VM_SIZE:-Standard_B2s}\"\nADMIN_USER=\"${ADMIN_USER:-azureuser}\"\nTAG_ENVIRONMENT=\"${TAG_ENVIRONMENT:-development}\"\n\n# Log resolved configuration (redact secrets)\ncat <<EOF\nConfiguration:\n  Subscription : $AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID\n  Resource Group: $TARGET_RG\n  Location      : $LOCATION\n  VM Size       : $VM_SIZE\n  Environment   : $TAG_ENVIRONMENT\nEOF\n\naz account set --subscription \"$AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID\" "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Structured JSON Output for CI Systems"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nRG=\"${RG:-myRG}\"\nLOCATION=\"${LOCATION:-eastus}\"\nSA_NAME=\"sa$(date +%s | tail -c 8)\"\n\naz group create -n \"$RG\" -l \"$LOCATION\" --only-show-errors -o none\naz storage account create -n \"$SA_NAME\" -g \"$RG\" \\\n  --sku Standard_LRS --only-show-errors -o none\n\n# Emit machine-readable result for CI to parse\nENDPOINT=$(az storage account show -n \"$SA_NAME\" -g \"$RG\" \\\n  --query primaryEndpoints.blob -o tsv)\n\n# JSON output for downstream pipeline steps\nprintf '{\"status\":\"ok\",\"rg\":\"%s\",\"storage_account\":\"%s\",\"blob_endpoint\":\"%s\"}\\n' \\\n  \"$RG\" \"$SA_NAME\" \"$ENDPOINT\" "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cross-Subscription and Cross-Tenant Scripts"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Enterprise scripts often span multiple subscriptions or tenants. The CLI maintains a context (active subscription) that must be managed explicitly when iterating across subscriptions."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\n# Iterate all subscriptions available to the logged-in identity\naz account list --query \"[?state=='Enabled'].id\" -o tsv |\nwhile read -r sub_id; do\n  echo \"=== Subscription: $sub_id ===\"\n  # Switch context for this subscription\n  az account set --subscription \"$sub_id\"\n  \n  # Run operations against the now-active subscription\n  az vm list --query \"[*].{name:name,rg:resourceGroup,size:hardwareProfile.vmSize}\" \\\n    -o table\ndone\n\n# Restore context after loop\naz account set --subscription \"${AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID:-$(az account show --query id -o tsv)}\"\n\n# Multi-tenant: log in to another tenant without affecting the current login\naz login --tenant \"other-tenant.onmicrosoft.com\" --allow-no-subscriptions 2>/dev/null\n# Run commands in that tenant context, then switch back\naz logout --username \"$(az account show --query user.name -o tsv)\" 2>/dev/null || true"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Debugging and Logging in Scripts"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a script fails in CI, you need enough context to reproduce the failure locally. Structured logging and the CLI's own debug flags make troubleshooting tractable."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Adding Timestamps and Structured Logs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\n# Logging helper: timestamp + severity + message\nlog() {\n  local level=$1; shift\n  printf '[%s] [%s] %s\\n' \"$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)\" \"$level\" \"$*\" >&2\n}\n\nlog INFO  \"Starting deployment for RG=$RG\"\nlog DEBUG \"Azure CLI version: $(az version --query '\"azure-cli\"' -o tsv)\"\n\n# Redirect only CLI errors to stderr; keep stdout for captured values\nWEBAPP_ID=$(az webapp show -g \"$RG\" -n myApp --query id -o tsv 2>&1) || {\n  log ERROR \"Failed to get webapp ID. az output: $WEBAPP_ID\"\n  exit 1\n}\n\nlog INFO \"Webapp ID: $WEBAPP_ID\"\nlog INFO \"Deployment complete\" "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Using --debug and --verbose"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# --debug emits HTTP request/response details \u2014 useful for API investigation\naz storage account create -g myRG -n mysa --sku Standard_LRS --debug 2>&1 | head -50\n\n# --verbose shows warnings and informational messages without full debug noise\naz webapp deploy -g myRG -n myApp --src-path app.zip --verbose\n\n# Redirect debug output to a log file while keeping normal stdout clean\naz group deployment create -g myRG --template-file main.bicep \\\n  --debug 2>deploy-debug.log\necho \"Debug log written to deploy-debug.log\"\n\n# In CI: enable debug only when a flag is set\nif [[ \"${AZURE_CLI_DEBUG:-}\" == \"1\" ]]; then\n  export AZURE_CLI_DEBUG_FLAGS=\"--debug\"\nelse\n  export AZURE_CLI_DEBUG_FLAGS=\"\"\nfi\naz vm create -g myRG -n myVM --image Ubuntu2204LTS $AZURE_CLI_DEBUG_FLAGS"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Azure CLI in Common CI/CD Platforms"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each CI/CD platform handles secrets and authentication differently. The pattern is consistent: authenticate with a service principal or managed identity, then run az commands as normal."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GitHub Actions"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/provision.yml\nname: Provision Azure Resources\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n\njobs:\n  provision:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Azure Login\n        uses: azure/login@v2\n        with:\n          creds: ${{ secrets.AZURE_CREDENTIALS }}\n          # AZURE_CREDENTIALS is the JSON output of:\n          # az ad sp create-for-rbac --role Contributor --scopes /subscriptions/<id> --sdk-auth\n\n      - name: Run provisioning script\n        env:\n          RG: ${{ vars.AZURE_RG }}\n          LOCATION: ${{ vars.AZURE_LOCATION }}\n        run: bash scripts/provision.sh\n\n      - name: Azure Logout\n        if: always()\n        run: az logout"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Azure DevOps Pipelines"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# azure-pipelines.yml\ntrigger:\n  branches:\n    include: [main]\n\npool:\n  vmImage: ubuntu-latest\n\nsteps:\n  - task: AzureCLI@2\n    displayName: 'Provision resources'\n    inputs:\n      azureSubscription: 'myServiceConnection'   # ARM service connection name\n      scriptType: bash\n      scriptLocation: scriptPath\n      scriptPath: scripts/provision.sh\n      arguments: '--env production'\n      addSpnToEnvironment: true    # Injects servicePrincipalId, servicePrincipalKey\n    env:\n      RG: $(AZURE_RG)\n      LOCATION: $(AZURE_LOCATION)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Caching the CLI Login in Self-Hosted Runners"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# For self-hosted runners using a managed identity, no login step is needed:\n# The runner VM's identity is used automatically.\naz vm list -o table    # works without az login on an identity-enabled VM\n\n# For service principal auth in scripts (no interactive login):\naz login \\\n  --service-principal \\\n  --username \"$AZURE_CLIENT_ID\" \\\n  --password \"$AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET\" \\\n  --tenant \"$AZURE_TENANT_ID\" \\\n  --output none\n\n# Or use a certificate (avoids secrets in environment variables):\naz login \\\n  --service-principal \\\n  --username \"$AZURE_CLIENT_ID\" \\\n  --certificate /run/secrets/sp-cert.pem \\\n  --tenant \"$AZURE_TENANT_ID\" \\\n  --output none"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
